<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="580" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1163,1548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1235,1260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of body 
<quantity box="[510,649,1235,1260]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="4.6" valueMax="5.1" valueMin="4.1">4.1–5.1 mm</quantity>
; length of fore wing 
<quantity box="[886,1025,1235,1260]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.6 mm</quantity>
; antenna yellowish brown; length of eye in dorsal view 
<number box="[384,433,1271,1296]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="1.25">1.25</number>
× as long as temple height (
<figureCitation box="[774,847,1271,1296]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,902,924]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,193,877]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[245,1341,193,880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helorus ruficornis Förster, 1856. A. Dorsal aspect of head, B. dorsal aspect of mesosoma, C. Dorsal aspect of metasoma, D. Lateral aspect of metasoma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244911/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[832,847,1272,1296]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A); mesoscutum punctate, notauli deep and finely crenulate (
<figureCitation box="[269,337,1307,1332]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,902,924]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,193,877]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[245,1341,193,880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helorus ruficornis Förster, 1856. A. Dorsal aspect of head, B. dorsal aspect of mesosoma, C. Dorsal aspect of metasoma, D. Lateral aspect of metasoma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244911/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[321,337,1308,1332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B); propodeum reticulate; pterostigma stout, 
<number box="[840,925,1307,1332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="2.5" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.6</number>
× as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1135,1201,1307,1332]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[195,1386,201,1527]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[194,1390,193,1532]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Helorus ruficornis Foerster, 1856. A. Lateral aspect of male general habitus, B. Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244910/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[1187,1201,1308,1332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B); legs (except hind coxa) yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[427,496,1343,1368]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,902,924]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,193,877]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[245,1341,193,880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helorus ruficornis Förster, 1856. A. Dorsal aspect of head, B. dorsal aspect of mesosoma, C. Dorsal aspect of metasoma, D. Lateral aspect of metasoma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244911/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[481,496,1344,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A); first metasomal segment slender, in dorsal and lateral view 
<number box="[1215,1278,1344,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="3.15" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.0">3–3.3</number>
times as long as its maximum width (
<figureCitation box="[414,486,1379,1404]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,902,924]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,193,877]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[245,1341,193,880]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helorus ruficornis Förster, 1856. A. Dorsal aspect of head, B. dorsal aspect of mesosoma, C. Dorsal aspect of metasoma, D. Lateral aspect of metasoma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244911/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
Figs 
<number box="[471,486,1380,1404]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<number box="[517,532,1380,1404]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
D); syntergite basally slender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
